                    <row>
                        
                        <cell>SUBJECT</cell>
                        <cell cols="2">Orientation of New Members</cell>
                    </row>
                    
                </table>
                
                
<p>An orientation session for the new Members of the Board was held, in Open Session, from 2:45 to 4:05 p.m. on 
    Thursday, <date value="2002-05-30">May 30, 2002</date>, in the Lower West Oval Room of the Rotunda. All five new Members were present: 
    <name type="present">Mark J. Kington, Don R. Pippin, Warren M. Thompson, E. Darracott Vaughan, Jr., M.D., and H. Timothy Lovelace, Jr.</name>, 
    the Student Member. The Rector, <name type="present">John P. Ackerly, III, and the President, John T. Casteen, III</name>, presided; 
    <name type="present">Leonard W. Sandridge, Gene D. Block, Paul J. Forch and Alexander G. Gilliam, Jr.</name> participated.</p>

<p>The orientation was conducted according to the following Agenda:</p>
                
                <list>
                    <item>1. Overall view of the Board, its Committee structure and its workings (<name type="person">Mr. Ackerly</name>)</item><lb/>
                    <item>2. The Organization Table of the University: How the University works and who the players are
                        (<name type="person">Mr. Casteen</name>)</item><lb/>
                    <item>3. An overview of the University's Budget (<name type="person">Mr. Sandridge</name>)</item><lb/>

                </list>
                <pb n="2."/>
                <p>2002 Orientation Minutes</p>	
            <list>
                <item>4. The University and State Appropriations (<name type="person">Mr. Casteen and Mr. Sandridge</name>)</item><lb/>
                <item>5. The University's overall rankings in comparison with its peers; the determining factors and the Board's role (<name type="person">Mr. Casteen</name> with comments by <name type="person">Mr. Block</name>)</item><lb/>
                <item>6. The duties and workings of the Board in the context of the Virginia Freedom of Information Act (<name type="person">Mr. Forch</name>)</item><lb/>
                <item>7. A brief miscellany of Board housekeeping matters (<name type="person">Mr. Gilliam</name>)</item>
                </list>
